  "isDnd":false,
  "layers":[
    {"$GMRAssetLayer":"","%Name":"Instructions","assets":[
        {"$GMRSpriteGraphic":"v1","%Name":"graphic_7CAF24E3_1","animationSpeed":1.0,"colour":4294967295,"frozen":false,"headPosition":0.0,"ignore":false,"inheritedItemId":null,"inheritItemSettings":false,"name":"graphic_7CAF24E3_1","resourceType":"GMRSpriteGraphic","resourceVersion":"2.0","rotation":0.0,"scaleX":64.0,"scaleY":36.0,"spriteId":{"name":"spr_Overlay","path":"sprites/spr_Overlay/spr_Overlay.yy",},"x":0.0,"y":0.0,},
        {"$GMRTextItem":"v3","%Name":"text_35350D58_1","alignment":0,"charSpacing":0.0,"colour":4283809600,"fontId":{"name":"fnt_Title","path":"fonts/fnt_Title/fnt_Title.yy",},"frameH":40.0,"frameW":600.0,"frozen":false,"ignore":false,"inheritedItemId":null,"inheritItemSettings":false,"lineSpacing":0.0,"name":"text_35350D58_1","paragraphSpacing":0.0,"resourceType":"GMRTextItem","resourceVersion":"2.0","rotation":0.0,"scaleX":1.0,"scaleY":1.0,"text":"TABLE FORMATTER DEMO","wrap":true,"x":20.0,"y":20.0,},
        {"$GMRTextItem":"v3","%Name":"text_2817D061_1","alignment":0,"charSpacing":0.0,"colour":4294967295,"fontId":{"name":"fnt_Info","path":"fonts/fnt_Info/fnt_Info.yy",},"frameH":600.0,"frameW":1240.0,"frozen":false,"ignore":false,"inheritedItemId":null,"inheritItemSettings":false,"lineSpacing":0.0,"name":"text_2817D061_1","paragraphSpacing":0.0,"resourceType":"GMRTextItem","resourceVersion":"2.0","rotation":0.0,"scaleX":1.0,"scaleY":1.0,"text":"This demonstration showcases the Strewt writing functionality.\r\n\r\nAt its core is a Strewt writer, writing the given text and managing indentations.\r\nThere is also a Strewt formatter, wrapping the writer and building up the actual result.\r\nBecause the formatter implements a Task Processor interface, the process can be spread over multiple frames.\r\n\r\nThis specific demonstration showcases formatting table-like data. The input must be an array of structs, and each struct must have only string/numeric/undefined entries.\r\nBoth the example and custom inputs are read from JSON files.\r\nReal-world formatter applications are likely to use runtime-generated entities as the input instead.\r\n\r\nYou can process one of preset examples or choose a custom file to load the input from (custom files are unavailable in the web demo).\r\nAlso, you can choose the processing speed (how much time is spent parsing each frame, in milliseconds).\r\nFinally, you can cancel an ongoing formatting process. It's easier to test with large example and low processing speed; otherwise, the processing finishes too quickly to be cancelled.\r\n\r\nFor certain data - in particular the large examples - the result output will be too large to fit in its window. In such case, you can scroll through it by:\r\n- using mouse wheel when hovering the panel\r\n- holding mouse left button near the top or bottom area of the panel\r\n- holding Up and Down keyboard buttons\r\n- pressing Page Up and Page Down keyboard buttons\r\n\r\nAll examples were made by hand.","wrap":true,"x":20.0,"y":80.0,},
      ],"depth":0,"effectEnabled":true,"effectType":null,"gridX":32,"gridY":32,"hierarchyFrozen":false,"inheritLayerDepth":false,"inheritLayerSettings":false,"inheritSubLayers":true,"inheritVisibility":true,"layers":[],"name":"Instructions","properties":[],"resourceType":"GMRAssetLayer","resourceVersion":"2.0","userdefinedDepth":false,"visible":false,},
    {"$GMRInstanceLayer":"","%Name":"Instances","depth":100,"effectEnabled":true,"effectType":null,"gridX":20,"gridY":20,"hierarchyFrozen":false,"inheritLayerDepth":false,"inheritLayerSettings":false,"inheritSubLayers":true,"inheritVisibility":true,"instances":[
